  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense that can result in significant legal consequences, including:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Felony charges\n- Potential prison time (usually 5-20 years)\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Heavy fines\n- Potential seizure of assets\n- Monetary penalties based on the amount laundered\n\n3. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil asset forfeiture\n- Mandatory restitution\n\n4. Additional Potential Outcomes\n- Deportation for non-citizens\n- Loss of voting rights\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Probation or supervised release\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money involved\n- Complexity of the laundering scheme\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction and specific laws\n\nProsecution typically involves law enforcement agencies like the FBI, IRS, and federal prosecutors.",
